396
00:37:55,160 --> 00:38:00,598
But we expected it to stop when
he could afford to start carrying.

397
00:38:00,680 --> 00:38:04,798
- Maybe we could hang out later?
- Sure.

398
00:38:04,880 --> 00:38:09,431
Yeah? We'll go out. I'll see you
when you get out of school.

399
00:38:09,520 --> 00:38:11,829
All right.

400
00:38:12,120 --> 00:38:15,271
Did you see that?
That's right.

401
00:38:21,200 --> 00:38:26,399
It's the time of the season

402
00:38:26,480 --> 00:38:29,438
when love runs high

403
00:38:29,520 --> 00:38:34,719
in this time give it to me easy

404
00:38:35,000 --> 00:38:39,118
and let me try
with pleasured hands

405
00:38:39,200 --> 00:38:43,193
to take you in the sun
to promised lands

406
00:38:43,280 --> 00:38:45,396
to show you every one

407
00:38:45,480 --> 00:38:52,238
it's the time of the season
for loving

408
00:38:56,880 --> 00:39:00,839
When we were in the mood for it
we had a parade.

409
00:39:01,120 --> 00:39:05,511
We wore our Dandy parade uniforms
showing off our true selves-

410
00:39:05,600 --> 00:39:09,195
- without fear of
what others may think.

411
00:39:29,560 --> 00:39:34,156
And under all those colors
was the seriousness of it all.

412
00:39:34,240 --> 00:39:37,471
For me anyway.

413
00:39:39,040 --> 00:39:42,555
And you, Wendy.

414
00:39:42,640 --> 00:39:46,394
I was so happy you were my friend.

415
00:39:46,480 --> 00:39:49,074
My confidante.

416
00:40:51,200 --> 00:40:53,634
You did it!

417
00:40:57,560 --> 00:41:01,314
Firing blind. It's incredible.

418
00:41:08,440 --> 00:41:12,228
- Congratulations, Dick.
- Thank you.

419
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:15,471
And they gave me a Dandy's
greatest accolade.

420
00:41:15,560 --> 00:41:19,235
Co-co-co-congratulations
D- d-dick!

421
00:41:19,320 --> 00:41:25,316
They congratulated me with the
special Brideshead stutter.

422
00:41:25,400 --> 00:41:29,951
Wendy thanks you, too.
We did this together.

423
00:41:32,360 --> 00:41:35,875
I felt as though you could have
hit that target without me.

424
00:41:36,160 --> 00:41:42,269
One thing's for sure.
I couldn't have done it without you.

425
00:41:42,360 --> 00:41:46,558
But I suppose
that's what friends are for.

426
00:41:46,640 --> 00:41:49,837
To complement each other.

427
00:41:50,120 --> 00:41:53,590
We were one, Wendy.

428
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:12,239
- Officer Krugsby.
- Hey there, Richard.

429
00:42:12,320 --> 00:42:16,871
- Mind if I come in?
- No, of course not. Please.

430
00:42:16,960 --> 00:42:22,114
Our procession last night may have
been a little provoking. Sorry...

431
00:42:22,200 --> 00:42:27,513
No, no problem. You're a good kid
I've known that for ages.

432
00:42:27,600 --> 00:42:33,709
Guys who like Aunt Mable's chocolate
muffins can't be all that bad.

433
00:42:33,800 --> 00:42:39,397
But I brought this guy with me.
