I'm good.

463
00:45:02,080 --> 00:45:06,551
- I read the book that you gave me.
- Shut the fuck up!

464
00:45:08,200 --> 00:45:12,512
One word from you
and it's back to jail with him.

465
00:45:12,600 --> 00:45:16,718
- And he will do exactly as I say?
- Of course.

466
00:45:17,000 --> 00:45:20,834
Why else
would I need a probation officer?

467
00:45:21,960 --> 00:45:26,795
- You gotta trust the little guy.
- I don't understand what he means.

468
00:45:26,880 --> 00:45:31,670
But I think we have an agreement.
Why don't we just...

469
00:45:32,960 --> 00:45:38,034
I think we've worked it out.
You're a good boy.

470
00:45:55,400 --> 00:46:01,589
Krugsby's plan was that Sebastian
checked in with me once a week.

471
00:46:02,800 --> 00:46:06,554
I decided to trust him
and save him.

472
00:46:06,640 --> 00:46:11,714
For Clarabelle, for Krugsby
for my belief in the little guy?

473
00:46:11,800 --> 00:46:17,716
Maybe just to prove that
I could make a Dandy out of him.

474
00:46:18,000 --> 00:46:21,834
A pacifist out of a murderer.

475
00:46:26,360 --> 00:46:28,920
Hello!

476
00:46:53,640 --> 00:46:56,074
Sebastian?

477
00:46:59,160 --> 00:47:02,436
You're here. Come on in.

478
00:47:04,880 --> 00:47:06,871
Well...

479
00:47:07,160 --> 00:47:11,199
- They're waiting in the library.
- The library?

480
00:47:11,280 --> 00:47:15,751
- You don't like reading?
- I got a book once.

481
00:47:15,840 --> 00:47:19,310
It's right down there.

482
00:47:23,240 --> 00:47:28,314
- They're doing the floret.
- Try and get a little more direct.

483
00:47:28,400 --> 00:47:30,709
Floret?

484
00:47:37,600 --> 00:47:43,948
OK, that's good. Maybe we
should try the first bit again.

485
00:47:45,360 --> 00:47:49,717
- And... one. That's better.
- Ahem.

486
00:47:49,800 --> 00:47:52,712
Excuse me.

487
00:47:52,800 --> 00:47:56,713
Hi, Sebastian.
Welcome to The Temple.

488
00:47:57,000 --> 00:48:02,870
You caught me in the middle of a
rehearsal. Come and meet the others.

489
00:48:02,960 --> 00:48:09,513
This is Stevie Dandelion. He's
working on a piece of ammunition.

490
00:48:09,600 --> 00:48:14,799
This particular gun
is named Bad Steel.

491
00:48:15,080 --> 00:48:18,595
It's got a shady past.

492
00:48:18,680 --> 00:48:21,752
It refused to fire
at a really dumb moment.

493
00:48:21,840 --> 00:48:25,799
Only because no one ever
looked after it properly.

494
00:48:26,080 --> 00:48:29,356
That's very true.

495
00:48:29,440 --> 00:48:32,398
Is there a problem?

496
00:48:32,480 --> 00:48:36,712
- You're wearing a turban.
- And?

497
00:48:37,000 --> 00:48:38,831
Nothing.

498
00:48:38,920 --> 00:48:42,708
Come on, let's meet the others.

499
00:48:43,000 --> 00:48:47,437
- Take care, Sebastian.
- You too, buddy.

500
00:48:47,520 --> 00:48:54,710
Hey, Freddie! Tell Sebastian about
the trick of the Moro warriors.

501
00:48:54,800 --> 00:48:58,793
They tied leather straps around their
testicles before going into battle.

502
00:48:59,080 --> 00:49:03,676
The pain used to make them
unstoppable by practically any gun.

503
00:49:03,760 --> 00:49:07,435
They fought 1000 percent.

504
00:49:07,520 --> 00:49:11,274
- That's some percentage.
- They were tough guys, Sebastian.

505
00:49:11,360 --> 00:49:14,557
Take a seat, please.

506
00:49:16,920 --> 00:49:20,435
- I came to check in.
- Yeah...

507
00:49:23,360 --> 00:49:25,590
Here I am.

508
00:49:25,680 --> 00:49:30,470
Your probation officer has nothing
special to tell you at this time.

509
00:49:30,560 --> 00:49:33,950
I just gotta ask if you stayed
away from firearms.

510
00:49:37,600 --> 00:49:41,991
- Yes, I have.
- That's good. Guns are bad news.

511
00:49:43,920 --> 00:49:48,789
- Yeah, they're bad news.
- Well, what do you think?

512
00:49:48,880 --> 00:49:53,431
- You guys are completely nuts.
- That's one way of looking at it.

513
00:49:53,520 --> 00:49:57,832
But it's what we've chosen
to spend our time on.

514
00:49:57,920 --> 00:50:02,152
I actually brought you here to
ask you if you'd like to join us.

515
00:50:03,720 --> 00:50:07,713
Might like to join you guys?

516
00:50:08,000 --> 00:50:12,790
- If I would like to join you?
- That's what I said.

517
00:50:13,120 --> 00:50:16,317
Let me think about it.

518
00:50:16,400 --> 00:50:21,155
- Like hell I would.
- Not even if you could have a gun?

519
00:50:26,440 --> 00:50:29,876
Your job is to make sure
that I don't get one.

520
00:50:30,160 --> 00:50:32,628
If you learn to be a Dandy-

521
00:50:32,720 --> 00:50:38,317
- and you're good enough, I'll make
sure you get the gun you want.

522
00:50:38,400 --> 00:50:43,872
But it will only be here.
And we'll do it our way.

523
00:50:43,960 --> 00:50:47,191
Just show up here every week.

524
00:50:47,280 --> 00:50:51,273
When we all think your attitude
is decent, you'll get that gun.

525
00:50:51,360 --> 00:50:55,239
Is shooting guys in the head decent?
No?

526
00:50:55,320 --> 00:51:00,440
Doing it isn't. Not doing it is what
makes us stronger and better.

527
00:51:00,520 --> 00:51:03,114
Can I go now?

528
00:51:03,200 --> 00:51:07,318
Your visit has been satisfactory.
I'll tell Krugsby.

529
00:51:07,400 --> 00:51:10,437
I'll see you here every Tuesday.

530
00:51:10,520 --> 00:51:13,034
Let me take a look at that.

531
00:51:15,720 --> 00:51:20,510
Small but no weakling.
She's one cute chick, man.

532
00:51:24,040 --> 00:51:27,874
More dangerous
than she looks, though.

533
00:51:32,680 --> 00:51:36,798
Doesn't she ever get tired
of your goofing around?

534
00:51:38,760 --> 00:51:45,199
Or with you? I'll bet you're way
too nice for her. See you Tuesday.

535
00:52:01,360 --> 00:52:06,229
I stood there for a moment
unable to speak.

536
00:52:06,320 --> 00:52:11,189
That self-assured way he held you.
And you enjoyed it.

537
00:52:11,280 --> 00:52:16,832
Just lying there in his hand.
I could see that. Cute girl.

538
00:52:16,920 --> 00:52:21,710
I decided that you would never
lay in his palm again.

539
00:52:21,800 --> 00:52:27,557
He was coarse and far from our
sophisticated image of a Dandy.

540
00:52:27,640 --> 00:52:34,159
"If I'd been a Dandy, I'd be dead,"
he said. Not the guy he shot.

541
00:52:34,240 --> 00:52:37,118
If he hadn't drawn his gun.

542
00:52:40,240 --> 00:52:44,119
He was up all night
so it's no wonder he's sleepy.

543
00:52:44,200 --> 00:52:47,795
- But he's real cute.
- He's cute?

544
00:52:48,080 --> 00:52:51,868
Cute? What do you mean?

545
00:52:51,960 --> 00:52:56,875
- Susan? I think I'm real cute.
- Kind of gorgeous.

546
00:52:58,640 --> 00:53:03,156
He's tough. And sexy.

547
00:53:03,240 --> 00:53:05,310
OK. So...

548
00:53:05,400 --> 00:53:10,838
Gorgeous. I'd always had trouble
seeing whether a man was gorgeous.

549
00:53:10,920 --> 00:53:15,994
I could see that he was strong.
And brown.

550
00:53:19,600 --> 00:53:23,718
I wondered if you had the
same experience as Susan.

551
00:53:24,000 --> 00:53:29,791
That you had shared a flirt.
You and Sebastian.

552
00:53:29,880 --> 00:53:33,873
You have a particular taste
in guys, I can see that.

553
00:53:34,160 --> 00:53:38,790
You like guys with big schlongs.
And I know he has a big schlongs.

554
00:53:38,880 --> 00:53:43,670
You deserve to have your mouth
washed out with soap.

555
00:53:43,760 --> 00:53:46,832
- Hey, Sebastian.
- Christmas comes early.

556
00:53:47,120 --> 00:53:52,478
Open it, it's for you.
Go ahead, don't be shy.

557
00:53:52,560 --> 00:53:55,632
A little Christmas gift for you.

558
00:53:55,720 --> 00:53:59,110
- There you go, man.
- Whoa!

559
00:53:59,200 --> 00:54:03,796
There you go.
It's what they had in the window.

560
00:54:03,880 --> 00:54:06,599
I'm a nice guy, you know.

561
00:54:06,680 --> 00:54:09,399
It's the nicest thing
anybody could ever do.

562
00:54:09,480 --> 00:54:15,828
No more talk about that gun down
town. Is that it? It was real cheap.

563
00:54:16,120 --> 00:54:20,033
- The 7.65 mm model 1900 automatic.
- Hey, hey, hey!

564
00:54:23,560 --> 00:54:28,509
I was tired of seeing Freddie being
beat up. Dandies don't get beat up.

565
00:54:28,600 --> 00:54:34,277
- Ain't that right, Dicky?
- Yeah, I guess so.

566
00:54:34,360 --> 00:54:39,115
That's the nicest thing. I can't
even believe these other guns.

567
00:54:39,200 --> 00:54:40,679
That's how I do it, girl.

568
00:54:41,000 --> 00:54:45,312
Do you, Freddie Dandelion
take this firearm -

569
00:54:45,400 --> 00:54:49,678
- in respect and honor
till death do you part?

570
00:54:49,760 --> 00:54:53,799
- I do.
- Perform the ritual.

571
00:55:05,360 --> 00:55:12,675
With these guns as witnesses, I hereby
wed thee, Freddie Dandelion, -

572
00:55:12,760 --> 00:55:15,672
- to this firearm.

573
00:55:20,320 --> 00:55:26,316
Co-co-co-congratulations
F- f-f-freddie!

574
00:55:26,400 --> 00:55:28,152
And...

575
00:55:28,480 --> 00:55:33,679
- Woman. Her name is Woman.
- Wo-wo-wo-woman!

576
00:56:03,480 --> 00:56:10,272
Dear Wendy
Sebastian was a hero.

577
00:56:10,360 --> 00:56:15,673
During the ceremony for Freddie and
Woman I couldn't take it anymore.

578
00:56:15,760 --> 00:56:19,594
I had to fight him.
But in a Dandy way.

579
00:56:19,680 --> 00:56:24,595
Sebastian hadn't been in the target
shaft. He had never seen us shoot.

580
00:56:25,640 --> 00:56:28,200
He'd never seen me shoot.

581
00:56:28,280 --> 00:56:31,716
That would be the perfect
Dandy way to show him-

582
00:56:31,800 --> 00:56:34,678
- who had the upper hand.

583
00:56:54,360 --> 00:56:58,239
All I had to do was to get up there
in front of the targets, -

584
00:56:58,320 --> 00:57:02,677
- pick you up from the partners'
waiting area with its blue velvet, -

585
00:57:02,760 --> 00:57:06,878
- and show off a few rounds
of relaxed hip shooting.

586
00:57:06,960 --> 00:57:09,633
And Sebastian would be blown away.

587
00:57:12,560 --> 00:57:17,395
Sebastian! What are you doing?

588
00:57:19,040 --> 00:57:24,319
Never touch another Dandy's gun.
That's rule number one.

589
00:57:29,800 --> 00:57:34,316
- My fault, boss.
- Why don't you just go?

590
00:57:34,400 --> 00:57:38,837
We don't want you here!
You come here and ruin everything!

591
00:57:38,920 --> 00:57:42,754
- At least he can aim.
- I don't care!

592
00:57:43,040 --> 00:57:46,476
- Susan, give me a scarf.
- Dick...

593
00:57:46,560 --> 00:57:50,633
I really think this is a bad idea.

594
00:57:59,040 --> 00:58:03,431
It's not nice to Wendy.

595
00:58:03,520 --> 00:58:07,752
Could I hear you, Wendy?

596
00:58:07,840 --> 00:58:11,674
Maybe I did sense some doubt
about our connection.

597
00:58:11,760 --> 00:58:16,436
But now it's time.

598
00:58:16,520 --> 00:58:20,513
It's you, Wendy... and me.

599
00:59:53,960 --> 00:59:57,236
- Hi.
- Hi again, Dick. How are you?

600
00:59:57,320 --> 01:00:03,111
I'm working on an idea that
would be right up Bad Steel's street.

601
01:00:03,200 --> 01:00:07,637
I came back to ask you to
perform a repair.

602
01:00:07,720 --> 01:00:11,838
- It's the sight.
- Does it need adjusting?

603
01:00:11,920 --> 01:00:15,469
You don't use the sight
you fire from the hip.

604
01:00:15,560 --> 01:00:20,156
That's exactly why I want it removed.

605
01:00:20,240 --> 01:00:25,633
I don't get it.
That's a very radical alteration.

606
01:00:25,720 --> 01:00:30,635
The sight is a major part of the
personality. You said so yourself.

607
01:00:30,720 --> 01:00:35,111
I've wanted it removed
for a long time.

608
01:00:36,360 --> 01:00:41,753
But if you don't use the sight
why should you care?

609
01:00:42,040 --> 01:00:46,636
- Only because others might use it.
- What are you talking about?

610
01:00:46,720 --> 01:00:50,793
This has got nothing to do
with Sebastian.

611
01:00:51,080 --> 01:00:56,393
- I didn't mention Sebastian.
- No. Are you gonna do it, or not?

612
01:01:39,680 --> 01:01:41,830
Wendy's my gun.

613
01:01:59,040 --> 01:02:02,794
I exchanged you for Emily.

614
01:02:04,800 --> 01:02:07,519
I closed myself up in the library, -

615
01:02:07,600 --> 01:02:10,876
- pretending to study my favorite
handbook on exit wounds.

616
01:02:11,160 --> 01:02:14,789
And not one of the Dandies
came up to comfort me.

617
01:02:15,080 --> 01:02:19,551
Until one did.
And as surprising as it sounds, -

618
01:02:19,640 --> 01:02:22,473
- it was Sebastian.

619
01:02:33,440 --> 01:02:36,159
Come on down, man.

620
01:02:44,720 --> 01:02:47,837
We're all worried about you.

621
01:02:47,920 --> 01:02:51,833
I've never liked you, Sebastian.

622
01:02:56,440 --> 01:03:01,116
What do you have
that I don't have?

623
01:03:01,200 --> 01:03:06,513
Maybe you're not
very good at understanding women.

624
01:03:06,600 --> 01:03:10,832
Or little lady revolvers
for that matter.

625
01:03:13,600 --> 01:03:19,277
In my experience, women may like
words, but they quickly forget them.

626
01:03:20,600 --> 01:03:25,390
- They want a bit of action.
- It's obvious that you'd say that.

627
01:03:25,480 --> 01:03:29,871
This pacifist stuff is real fancy
but it's easy too.

628
01:03:29,960 --> 01:03:33,748
I don't see it that way.
The others don't, either.

629
01:03:33,840 --> 01:03:40,678
Shut up. You might as well say
"I'm scared, I'll carry a gun."

630
01:03:40,760 --> 01:03:44,230
- I'm not scared.
- You sure as hell are.

631
01:03:44,320 --> 01:03:48,279
So am I. So is everybody else.

632
01:03:48,360 --> 01:03:51,875
The kids downstairs are scared too.

633
01:03:52,160 --> 01:03:56,711
Clara... Clarabelle is scared.

634
01:03:56,800 --> 01:04:00,236
Clarabelle?

635
01:04:00,320 --> 01:04:04,199
Clarabelle, as in your grandma?

636
01:04:04,280 --> 01:04:08,671
She suddenly got real old.
She can't remember a damn thing.

637
01:04:10,400 --> 01:04:14,678
She doesn't even dare to
go outside her door anymore.

638
01:04:14,760 --> 01:04:20,118
The last few years she's only been
out on one single day a year.

639
01:04:20,200 --> 01:04:24,876
One day.
On Cynthia's birthday.

640
01:04:26,520 --> 01:04:30,195
But she doesn't dare, this year.

641
01:04:30,280 --> 01:04:36,310
She thinks these gangs will kill her
steal her coffee, rob her...

642
01:04:39,120 --> 01:04:44,433
Which is obviously a delusion.
She lost it, man.

643
01:04:44,520 --> 01:04:48,752
Dear Wendy
An idea for a plan appeared to me.

644
01:04:48,840 --> 01:04:53,595
A plan that would prove that the
Dandies were not just about words.

645
01:04:53,680 --> 01:04:58,310
Proof. For them.
And for you, Wendy.

646
01:05:07,120 --> 01:05:10,157
Hi. Please come in.

647
01:05:17,800 --> 01:05:23,238
We're going to have an exercise.
An important exercise.

648
01:05:23,320 --> 01:05:29,156
Sebastian told me there's an
old woman living on the square.

649
01:05:29,240 --> 01:05:33,518
She wants to visit her cousin
but is too scared.

650
01:05:33,600 --> 01:05:40,119
We're going to prove to that the
strength of the Dandies exists...

651
01:05:41,800 --> 01:05:45,315
...and is completely intact.

652
01:05:47,080 --> 01:05:53,679
Through our presence, the old lady
who is Sebastian's grandmother...

653
01:05:53,760 --> 01:05:56,752
- Really?
- Yeah.

654
01:05:57,040 --> 01:06:00,350
She will have the courage to
cross the square.

655
01:06:00,440 --> 01:06:06,276
Our strength will rub off on her.

656
01:06:06,360 --> 01:06:12,754
And after this exercise I think we'll
believe in everything a lot more.

657
01:06:14,440 --> 01:06:19,798
And besides
it'll be a good deed.

658
01:06:21,200 --> 01:06:24,829
Your granny?
The lady with the giant purse?

659
01:06:24,920 --> 01:06:29,596
- Huge purse.
- How awful. Not daring to go out.

660
01:06:29,680 --> 01:06:33,355
- It's terrible.
- Will our partners be with us?

661
01:06:33,440 --> 01:06:38,195
They will come along
as our moral support.

662
01:06:38,280 --> 01:06:44,435
- So what's our strategy?
- Well, I have a few ideas.

663
01:06:44,520 --> 01:06:49,799
We're here.
Opposite here is Susan's store, -

664
01:06:49,880 --> 01:06:52,792
- the new mine and the old mine.

665
01:06:53,080 --> 01:06:58,871
Clarabelle lives here. It's simple.
We'll take her through the Swamp, -

666
01:06:58,960 --> 01:07:04,796
- through East Side, Slope Corner
and the Shack to Cynthia's here.

667
01:07:04,880 --> 01:07:10,750
Freddie and Woman will stand here
for Clarabelle's safe arrival.

668
01:07:10,840 --> 01:07:15,516
Susan's Lee and Grant can keep
a sharp lookout down the street.

669
01:07:15,600 --> 01:07:19,752
Huey and Lyndon can create
peace and stability in East Side, -

670
01:07:20,040 --> 01:07:24,636
- Stevie and Bad Steel can cover
the long corners from Center Pole.

671
01:07:24,720 --> 01:07:27,712
Come here. Take a look.

672
01:07:28,000 --> 01:07:31,709
Sebastian, you're going to be
with me at Clarabelle's.

673
01:07:32,000 --> 01:07:35,834
Huey, you'll be in Zone 6
in front of the Swamp.

674
01:07:36,120 --> 01:07:39,715
Stevie, you can take Zone 8.

675
01:07:39,800 --> 01:07:44,430
They all looked at Electric Park
which they knew so well, -

676
01:07:44,520 --> 01:07:49,594
- and saw the square in a new light
as their square again.

677
01:07:49,680 --> 01:07:54,117
And it made us Dandies once more.
And together.

678
01:07:54,200 --> 01:07:58,318
So that's the plan.
Is everyone agreed?

679
01:08:14,520 --> 01:08:19,230
Cynthia had the coffee pot and the
cake ready for Clarabelle's visit.

680
01:08:19,320 --> 01:08:25,634
Down on the square, the Dandies
were ready to ensure her safety.

681
01:08:25,720 --> 01:08:29,679
So there was no need to worry.
This was an absolutely normal day.

682
01:08:32,960 --> 01:08:37,750
- Hi. We're ready downstairs.
- It's Dick!

683
01:08:38,040 --> 01:08:43,239
Hi, Clarabelle.
Do you remember me? Dicky?

684
01:08:43,320 --> 01:08:48,474
- I don't remember a damn thing!
- Should we go?

685
01:08:48,560 --> 01:08:51,597
- We should go.
- OK.

686
01:08:51,680 --> 01:08:56,231
The Imperial coffee.
It's a beautiful day outside too.

687
01:08:56,320 --> 01:09:00,791
Don't worry, Clarabelle.
Nothing is going to happen.

688
01:09:00,880 --> 01:09:04,509
Don't forget the keys, man.

689
01:09:04,600 --> 01:09:07,990
Let's go, Mommy.

690
01:09:09,320 --> 01:09:14,599
- All right... watch your step.
- Oh!

691
01:09:14,680 --> 01:09:17,911
It's gonna be all right.

692
01:09:20,560 --> 01:09:22,710
Oh dear...

693
01:09:22,800 --> 01:09:25,758
You're doing good, Clarabelle.

694
01:09:25,840 --> 01:09:28,912
See the window? It's right there.

695
01:09:37,640 --> 01:09:41,110
- My bag.
- Nobody is going to touch your bag.

696
01:09:46,040 --> 01:09:47,871
Look, it's Cynthia.

697
01:09:52,240 --> 01:09:55,949
I got my bag...

698
01:09:56,720 --> 01:09:59,632
- Oh!
- Hey!

699
01:09:59,720 --> 01:10:03,474
Ma'am! Let me help you get up.

